package exec_06_01_compiler_assignment_pattern_struct_mismatch

## Semantics: struct pattern mismatches yield an Error value (falsy).

struct Point { x: i32, y: i32 }
struct Other { x: i32 }

fn main() -> void {
  value := Other { x: 1 }
  if Point { x, y } := value {
    print("ok")
  } else {
    print("error")
  }
}
